<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1313">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 1313<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Secretary of War</hi>
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_SHL2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                            <gloss type="to">President</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-30">30 July
                                                1945.<note n="1" xml:id="d1313fn1"><persName corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName> had left
                                                Babelsberg on July 25 and had returned to
                                                Washington.</note></date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p><gloss target="#t_War1"><hi rend="smallcaps">War</hi></gloss>
                                    41011. To the President from the Secretary of <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss>.</p>
                                <p>The time schedule on <persName corresp="#p_GMGLR1">Groves</persName>’ project is progressing so rapidly that
                                    it is now essential that statement for release by you be
                                    available not later than Wednesday, 1 August. I have revised
                                    draft of statement, which I previously presented to you,<note n="2" xml:id="d1313fn2">The draft referred to has not been
                                        found.</note> in light of</p>
                                <pb facs="1573" n="1375" xml:id="pg_1375"/>
                                <list>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Your recent ultimatum,<note n="3" xml:id="d1313fn3"><ref target="#d1382">Document No.
                                        1382</ref>.</note></item>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Dramatic results of test and</item>
                                    <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                    <item>Certain minor suggestions made by British<note n="4" xml:id="d1313fn4">Not printed.</note> of which <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">Byrnes</persName> is aware.</item>
                                </list>
                                <p>While I am planning to start a copy by special courier tomorrow
                                    in the hope you can be reached, nevertheless in the event he
                                    does not reach you in time, I will appreciate having your
                                    authority to have White House release revised statement as soon
                                    as necessary.<note n="5" xml:id="d1313fn5">For the text of the
                                        statement as issued by the White House in Washington on
                                        August 6, see <ref target="#d1315">document No. 1315</ref>.
                                        Concerning the military orders issued from the Conference
                                        for the atomic attack on Japan, see Craven and Cate, eds.,
                                            <hi rend="italic">The Army Air Forces in World <gloss target="#t_War1">War</gloss> II</hi> vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, facsimile facing p. 697 and
                                        chapter 23.</note></p>
                                <p>Sorry circumstances seem to require this emergency action.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>